        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 4:25PM CDT until June 8 at 5:30PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Armstrong County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Carson County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southern Gray County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Northern Donley County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 530 PM CDT.

* At 425 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Groom, or 14
miles northeast of Claude, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

* Locations impacted include...
Lake Mcclellan, Lefors, Alanreed, Groom, and Mclean.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
